narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Computational system modeling, differential equation analysis, statistical techniques.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: This class had some of the coolest material I've seen, but the way it was presented was not very good. Lectures often lacked motivation and were confusing and boring. Psets were challenging, but helped to understand material well.

Unfortunately very few students came to class which was honestly the biggest weakness of this class (though this was not the instructor's fault). Over all, course taught a very comprehensive range of modeling techniques and was a great introduction to chaos theory. PSETs were of a perfect workload if you have previous experience in Python or MATLAB.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Absolutely, and I have recommended all my friends take it during their time at Yale. Not only is the subject matter super interesting, the Prof. Korenaga is a genius and has a great sense of humor. This is a bit of a "dark horse" class that few have taken, but provides a really great introduction to modeling various systems.
Highly would recommend this course to others -- Professor Korenaga is an amazing teacher, passionate about what his is teaching, and always willig to help.
